Authentication types
- Hashing, Encryption, Json Web Tokens & local storage.
What is Hashing?
- we hash password before we store in database. Hashing is one way process we can't convert it back to orignal.
what is Encryption?
- It is two way given the give the value convert to encrypted value & encrypted value convert to previous value. as long as we have password.
what is Json Web Tokens?
- It is neither of encryption or hashing (its technically a digital signature)
- Anyone can see the orignal output given the signature.
- Signature can be verified only using the password.
